==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapid
<hw>Sap"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sapidus</ets>,
fr. <ets>sapere</ets> to taste: cf. F. <ets>sapide</ets>. See
<er>Sapient</er>, <er>Savor</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the power of
affecting the organs of taste; possessing savor, or flavor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Camels, to make the water <qex>sapid</qex>, do raise the mud with
their feet.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapidity</ent>⟦br⟧
